[h1] Adding a comment section

[p-]
Any podweb page can have a built-in comment section. Readers can post a short
message directly inside the browser - no extra setup needed on your end.
[-p]

[h2] How to add it

[p] Place the tag anywhere in your .podweb file:

[code-]
[comments]
[-code]

[p-]
That is all. The browser renders a scrollable comment area with an input field
and a post button at the bottom of the block.
[-p]

[h2] How it works

[p-]
Comments are stored on podnet using the Picotron leaderboard system (scoresub).
Each page gets its own leaderboard table named after its URL. Because scoresub
keeps one entry per user, every reader can leave exactly one comment - posting
again replaces the previous one.
[-p]

[h2] Requirements

[p-]
Comments only work on podnet:// pages. The reader must also be logged in to
their Lexaloffle account inside Picotron. If either condition is not met the
browser shows a notice instead of the input field.
[-p]

[h2] Adjusting the height

[p] You can set a custom height in pixels for the comment block:

[code-]
[comments height=200]
[-code]

[p] The default height is 140 pixels.

